PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1782902882
OL,3,CPolice officers called to Henry Nowak
OL,4,Cmurder face gross misconduct
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,FTwo police officers called to the
OL,8,Fscene of Henry Nowak's murder are
OL,9,Funder investigation for potential
OL,10,Fgross misconduct after they failed to
OL,11,Fgive him immediate first aid and
OL,12,Finstead handcuffed him as he lay dying.
OL,14,FThe 18-year-old told officers he could
OL,15,Fnot breathe and that he had been
OL,16,Fstabbed after being attacked in
OL,17,FSouthampton on December 3 last year,
OL,18,Fbut officers from Hampshire
OL,19,FConstabulary ignored his pleas and
OL,20,Ffailed to realise he was mortally
OL,21,Finjured.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1782902882
OL,3,CPolice officers called to Henry Nowak
OL,4,Cmurder face gross misconduct
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,FThe Independent Office for Police
OL,8,FConduct (IOPC) said it is
OL,9,Finvestigating potential failures by
OL,10,Fthe officers to realise that Henry
OL,11,Fneeded urgent medical attention, to
OL,12,Ftake action when he said he had been
OL,13,Fstabbed and could not breathe, and the
OL,14,Fdecision to arrest and handcuff him
OL,15,Finstead of providing first aid.
OL,17,FOne of the officers is also under
OL,18,Finvestigation for potentially
OL,19,Fbreaching conduct standards by
OL,20,Fdismissing the teenager's claim that
OL,21,Fhe had been stabbed.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1782902882
OL,3,CPolice officers called to Henry Nowak
OL,4,Cmurder face gross misconduct
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,FThe watchdog is also looking at
OL,8,Fwhether race or religion played a part
OL,9,Fin the officers' decision making.
OL,11,FKiller Vickrum Digwa lied to police
OL,12,Fthat he had been the victim of a
OL,13,Fracist attack by Henry, when in fact
OL,14,Fhe had fatally stabbed the 18-year-old.
OL,16,FIOPC director of engagement Derrick
OL,17,FCampbell said: "We continue to extend
OL,18,Four deepest sympathies to Henry's
OL,19,Ffamily and friends.
OL,26,@yD@POU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1782902882
OL,3,CPolice officers called to Henry Nowak
OL,4,Cmurder face gross misconduct
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,F"Our investigators met with Henry's
OL,8,Ffamily earlier this month where we
OL,9,Fwere able to discuss our investigation
OL,10,Fwith them in depth, now that criminal
OL,11,Fproceedings have concluded.
OL,13,F"We are obliged to constantly review
OL,14,Fthe evidence obtained throughout our
OL,15,Finvestigations and assess any
OL,16,Findications of potential misconduct
OL,17,Ffor officers involved. As a result,
OL,18,Ftwo officers will now face gross
OL,19,Fmisconduct investigations.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1782902882
OL,3,CPolice officers called to Henry Nowak
OL,4,Cmurder face gross misconduct
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,F"There is clear evidence that public
OL,8,Fconfidence in the force may have been
OL,9,Fseriously harmed by this incident, and
OL,10,Fthat is a factor we must consider when
OL,11,Fassessing the evidence.
OL,13,F"The serving of gross misconduct
OL,14,Fnotices does not necessarily mean that
OL,15,Fdisciplinary proceedings will follow.
OL,16,FAt the end of our investigation, we
OL,17,Fwill decide whether any officers
OL,18,Fshould face disciplinary proceedings."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUzD@fO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1782902882
OL,3,CPolice officers called to Henry Nowak
OL,4,Cmurder face gross misconduct
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,FThe IOPC said it had expanded its
OL,8,Finvestigation following discussions
OL,9,Fwith Henry's family, who have lodged
OL,10,Fformal complaints about the force.
OL,12,FThe case sparked outrage and protests
OL,13,Fwhen Digwa was jailed for life for
OL,14,Fmurder in May, with Hampshire Police
OL,15,Ffacing accusations that officers had
OL,16,Ffailed to listen to Henry because he
OL,17,Fwas white.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1782902882
OL,3,CPolice officers called to Henry Nowak
OL,4,Cmurder face gross misconduct
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,FInvestigators from the IOPC are
OL,8,Flooking at whether the race or
OL,9,Freligion of Digwa, who is Sikh, or
OL,10,FHenry impacted on the decisions made,
OL,11,Fand whether officers "were influenced
OL,12,Fby assumptions or prejudice relating
OL,13,Fto community tensions at the time".
OL,15,FWhen Digwa was sentenced, Henry's
OL,16,Ffather Mark Nowak said the difference
OL,17,Fbetween the way the killer and his son
OL,18,Fwere treated was "unbearable".
OL,26,@sD@VOUuD@bO]zD@ROUzD@]O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1782902882
OL,3,CPolice officers called to Henry Nowak
OL,4,Cmurder face gross misconduct
OL,5,Cinvestigation
OL,7,FHe told journalists: "His murderer...
OL,8,Fwas afforded decency. He was believed.
OL,9,FHe was not handcuffed when arrested.
OL,10,FHe was not handcuffed when transported
OL,11,Fto the police station. As far as we
OL,12,Funderstand, he was never handcuffed at
OL,13,Fall.
OL,15,F"And, as Vickrum Digwa himself told
OL,16,Fthe court, while under arrest for
OL,17,FHenry's murder, police even took him
OL,18,Fto the kitchen so he could choose his
OL,19,Ffood.
OL,21,F"The contrast is unbearable."
OL,26,@oD@VOUwD@AOU}D@AOU}D@]O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/8
